cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

The paper is about a toolkit for Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks using Deep Neural Networks (DNN). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the flexibility and optimization mechanisms of the toolkit, which suggests that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of JSON files for configuration, which is a common practice in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted on NLP datasets also suggest that the paper could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
